cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.AI 

This paper deals with the security and networking aspects of IoT devices, which are typically covered under the Computer Science categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper discusses the development and verification of Manufacturer Usage Description (MUD) profiles for IoT devices, which is a security measure to lock down and verify their network behavior. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR, followed by cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SY, and cs.AI.
